As used in this section:
"Mixed-use" means a project:
That includes at least two (2) qualified uses; or
That meets the requirements established by paragraph (b)2.b. of this subsection;
"Qualified use" means:
Retail;
Residential;
Office;
Restaurant; or
Hospitality.
Except as otherwise provided in paragraph (b)2.b. of this subsection, to be a qualified use the use must comprise at least twenty percent (20%) of the total finished square footage of the proposed project or represent twenty percent (20%) of the total capital investment; and
In any location within the territory of a consolidated local government or an urban-county government, a project whose uses do not meet the requirements of paragraph (b)2.a. of this subsection may qualify as a mixed-use project if all of the following apply: i. The project includes at least three (3) of the uses listed in paragraph (b)1. of this subsection; ii. One (1) of those uses meets the requirements of paragraph (b)2.a. of this subsection; and iii. The other uses, when combined, jointly comprise at least twenty percent (20%) of the total finished square footage of the proposed project or represent twenty percent (20%) of the total capital investment; and
"Retail" means an establishment predominantly engaged in the sale of tangible personal property subject to the tax imposed by KRS Chapter 139, but shall not include restaurants.

To be considered for state participation under this program, a project shall:
Be located in an area that has three (3) or more of the conditions listed in KRS 65.7049(3)(a), or be a project described in KRS 65.7049(3)(b);
Be a mixed-use project;
Represent new economic activity in the Commonwealth;
Result in a capital investment between twenty million dollars ($20,000,000) and two hundred million dollars ($200,000,000);
Not include any retail establishment that exceeds twenty thousand (20,000) square feet of finished square footage;
Include pedestrian amenities and public space; and
Result in a net positive economic impact to the Commonwealth, taking into consideration any substantial adverse impact on existing Commonwealth businesses. The net positive impact shall be certified to the authority as required by KRS 154.30-030(6)(b).

As part of the approval process, the authority shall determine the following:
The footprint of the project;
That the proposed project meets the requirements established by subsection (4) of this section;
The maximum amount of approved public infrastructure costs and expenses for land preparation, demolition, and clearance;
That the local revenues pledged to support the public infrastructure of the project and local revenues pledged to support the overall project are of a sufficient amount to warrant participation of the Commonwealth in the project;
The termination date of the tax incentive agreement; and
Any adjustments to be made to old revenues, in determining incremental revenues during each year of the term of the tax incentive agreement.
